  "issue_title": "[BUG] Issue discovery credibility uses valid_solved_count instead of total solved_count - lowers credibility unfairly",
  "issue_body": "## Description\n\n`check_issue_eligibility` at `issue_discovery/scoring.py:62` receives `data.valid_solved_count`\nas its first parameter (line 131) and uses it for BOTH:\n\n1. The eligibility minimum check (correct \u2014 should use valid count)\n2. The credibility formula via `calculate_issue_credibility` (incorrect \u2014 should use total solved)\n\nThe credibility formula per the docs:\n\n    issue_credibility = solved_issues / (solved_issues + closed_issues - mulligan)\n\n\"Solved issues\" means ALL issues resolved via merged PRs, not just those where the solving\nPR has token_score >= 5. The OSS credibility implementation does this correctly \u2014 it passes\nall merged PRs to credibility and separately counts valid ones for the minimum check.\n\n## Impact\n\nA miner with 10 solved issues (7 valid, 3 with low token_score PRs) and 2 closed issues:\n- **Correct credibility**: 10 / (10 + max(0, 2-1)) = 10/11 = 0.91\n- **Current credibility**: 7 / (7 + max(0, 2-1)) = 7/8 = 0.875\n\nThe miner's credibility multiplier is 0.875 instead of 0.91 \u2014 a 4% scoring penalty\nfor having solved issues that happened to involve small PRs.\n\n## Root cause\n\nLine 131 passes `data.valid_solved_count` where `data.solved_count` should be used for\nthe credibility calculation:\n\n    is_eligible, credibility, reason = check_issue_eligibility(data.valid_solved_count, data.closed_count)\n\nThe OSS pattern separates these correctly (credibility.py:49-52):\n\n    credibility = calculate_credibility(merged_prs, closed_prs)\n    valid_merged_count = sum(1 for pr in merged_prs if pr.token_score >= MIN_TOKEN_SCORE_FOR_BASE_SCORE)\n\n## Evidence\n\n<img width=\"1436\" height=\"694\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/491de683-b143-4551-8da1-34380155df9e\" />",
